  "mixStrategy": "SLEEP MODE Electronic/House \u2014 Ultra-gentle, dark, warm, enveloping ambient wash. NO drums. Three tracks occupy distinct frequency bands to create a rich but sleepy sonic blanket.\n\nFREQUENCY SEPARATION:\n- BASS (Synth Bass, 20-300Hz, MIDI 33-45): Ultra-slow, quiet root notes with long sustains (4-8s). Provides a warm, dark foundation like a distant heartbeat. Plays chord roots only (A, D, F, G in low octaves). Velocity 25-40 \u2014 barely felt, more like a subsonic hum.\n- CHORDS (Warm Pad, 300Hz-2kHz, MIDI 48-67): Lush sustained minor chord voicings (8-16s sustains). These are the harmonic body \u2014 slow-moving, overlapping pads that breathe gently. Velocity 30-45. Voicings use root-3rd-5th with occasional 7ths for warmth.\n- MELODY (Sawtooth Lead used as soft high texture, 1kHz+, MIDI 64-79): Sparse, lonely high notes \u2014 one every 3-5 seconds. Like distant stars twinkling. Very low velocity (25-40). These are chord tones and gentle passing tones from A natural minor scale. No arpeggiation \u2014 just floating single notes.\n\nHARMONIC UNITY: All tracks follow the same slow progression: Am \u2192 Dm \u2192 F \u2192 G \u2192 Am \u2192 Dm \u2192 Am (i \u2192 iv \u2192 bVI \u2192 bVII \u2192 i \u2192 iv \u2192 i). Chord changes happen every ~6-8 seconds, giving each chord time to breathe and settle.\n\nENERGY ARC (6 segments, ~7.5s each):\nSeg1 (0-7.5s): 0.3 \u2014 Bass and pad fade in gently on Am. Melody silent or one note.\nSeg2 (7.5-15s): 0.4 \u2014 Dm chord, melody enters with sparse notes. Slightly fuller.\nSeg3 (15-22.5s): 0.5 \u2014 F chord, peak warmth. All three layers present but still whisper-quiet.\nSeg4 (22.5-30s): 0.5 \u2014 G chord, sustained gentle peak. Melody slightly more active.\nSeg5 (30-37.5s): 0.4 \u2014 Return to Am then Dm, energy receding. Melody thins.\nSeg6 (37.5-45s): 0.3 \u2014 Final Am, everything fades to near-silence. Long held tones dissolving.\n\nRHYTHMIC APPROACH: No rhythmic pulse. Everything floats freely with long overlapping sustains. This is ambient sleep music \u2014 time should feel suspended. Notes drift in and out like breathing.",
